It get's off it's home planet permanently.

The difference in scale of resource potential between a planet bound,
versus a (multi-)planetary system bound society are incomparable.

Issues of life-span are generaly irrelevant, the two technologies develop
hand in hand (there will of course be some synchronisation issues in
particular instances) and will offset any fundamental distance issue.

In general, such societies will be very rare.

